               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 5 items (a-e)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, doctrine, and poetry. Volume not dated; datable to late eighteenth century. Crude illumination at beginning. Scribal nastaʿlīq with naskh in the style of <persName key="viaf_51041763" role="oth">Aḥmad Nayrīzī</persName>. Stamped foliation. Binding damaged and detached from gathering; leather boards stitched into faded green coarse cotton cover or ghilāf with paper labels attached. Folios unbound and torn in parts, later repairs.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1028-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="5r">ff. 1v-5r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise on spiritual extinction or fanāʾ through union with God by <persName key="person_f7360" role="aut">Muḥammad ibn Abū Saʿīd al-Ḥasanī</persName>, but ascribed to <persName key="person_f7360" role="aut">Mīr Sayyid Muḥammad-i Kālpī</persName>, which is likely to be another form of address for the same author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Crude illuminated ʿunvān and interlineation at beginning (ff. 1v-2r). 
</p>
                        <p>Nastaʿlīq, with naskh in the Nayrīzī style for Arabic passages. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22190">Risālah dar bayān-i marātib-i fanāʾ</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7360"> Mīr Sayyid Muḥammad ibn Abū Saʿīd al-Ḥasanī Kālpī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1028-item2">
                     <locus from="5r" to="91r">ff. 5r-91r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise assembling miscellaneous Arabic supplications and litanies, with instructions for their use in Persian, by an unnamed compiler. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat naskh in the Nayrīzī style for Arabic passages. 
</p>
                        <p>Loose sheet of verses inserted between folios 60-61. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1028-item3">
                     <locus from="91r" to="112v">ff. 91r-112v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise recording the religious teachings of a certain <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657030.0x000001 viaf_305037823" role="ant">Sayyid Fatḥ ʿAlī Ḥusaynī Riz̤avī Gardīzī</persName> (active circa 1750) by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1028-item4">
                     <locus from="113r" to="116v">ff. 113r-116v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Brief treatise on mystical knowledge by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657030.0x000001 viaf_305037823" role="aut">Sayyid Fatḥ ʿAlī Ḥusaynī Riz̤avī Gardīzī</persName> (active circa 1750). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22191">Mirʾāt al-ʿirfān</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657030.0x000001 viaf_305037823" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Sayyid Fatḥ ʿAlī Ḥusaynī Riz̤avī Gardīzī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1028-item5">
                     <locus from="116v" to="128v">ff. 116v-128v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Apologia in defence of the theological stance adopted by the poet and diarist, <persName key="viaf_50013027" role="ant">Shaykh Muḥammad ʿAlī ibn Abū Ṭālib Muḥammad Lāhijī Gīlānī "Ḥazīn"</persName> (d. 1180/1766) in his poetry, written by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657030.0x000001 viaf_305037823" role="aut">Fatḥ ʿAlī Ḥusaynī Riz̤avī Gardīzī </persName>(active circa 1750). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work may be incomplete at end, as the text breaks off without appropriate conclusion or a colophon. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22192">Ibṭāl al-bāṭil</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657030.0x000001 viaf_305037823">Fatḥ ʿAlī Ḥusaynī Riz̤avī Gardīzī</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
